				\begin{document}$$\lambda$$\end{document}λ denotes the cost-effectiveness threshold, representing willingness to pay (WTP) for an additional QALY. PATHS was deemed cost effective at a given threshold if the INB was positive. INBs were estimated for thresholds ranging from £0 to 150,000, increasing in £1000 increments. In the UK, NICE sets this threshold at £20,000–30,000 [28].
